OL,3,CAsylum seekers who break law or work
OL,4,Cillegally to lose right to
OL,5,Caccommodation
OL,7,FLast year, a total of #4 billion was
OL,8,Fspent on asylum support in the UK, and
OL,9,Fas of December, there were 107,003
OL,10,Fpeople in receipt of asylum support,
OL,11,Fwith 30,657 in around 200 asylum
OL,12,Fhotels, the Home Office said.
OL,14,FThe issue of people being housed in
OL,15,Fhotels rose to prominence last year
OL,16,Fwith protests outside some sites.
OL,18,FLabour has pledged to no longer use
OL,19,Fasylum hotels by the end of this
OL,20,FParliament, which would be 2029, if
OL,21,Fnot earlier.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1772809880
OL,3,CAsylum seekers who break law or work
OL,4,Cillegally to lose right to
OL,5,Caccommodation
OL,7,FIn October, the government announced
OL,8,Fthat barracks in Scotland and southern
OL,9,FEngland would be used to house around
OL,10,F900 men temporarily, as part of
OL,11,Fgovernment efforts to stop using
OL,12,Fhotels to temporarily house asylum
OL,13,Fseekers.
OL,15,FIn November last year, Mahmood
OL,16,Fannounced changes that would make the
OL,17,FUK's immigration system one of the
OL,18,Ftoughest in Europe, taking inspiration
OL,19,Ffrom the Danish government.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1772809880
OL,3,CAsylum seekers who break law or work
OL,4,Cillegally to lose right to
OL,5,Caccommodation
OL,7,FThe changes are aimed at reducing the
OL,8,F"pull factors" that make people want
OL,9,Fto come to the UK, by making it harder
OL,10,Fto get permanent refugee status,
OL,11,Freducing barriers to deportation and
OL,12,Freforming human rights laws.
OL,14,FThe plans will see the time it takes
OL,15,Fmigrants to be able to apply for
OL,16,Fpermanent settled status doubled from
OL,17,Ffive to ten years, while refugees
OL,18,Fcould have to wait 20 years, and those
OL,19,Fwho arrive by small boat could wait up
OL,20,Fto 30 years for residency.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
